.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
size \- Get the number of records from the current cursor to the final cursor.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]\f[I]query.size()\f[]\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
SdbQuery
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Get the number of records from the current cursor to the final cursor.
.TE

\f[B]Note:\f[]
.RE
.PP
The result that size() return is influenced by skip() and limit().
.RE
.SH PARAMETERS
.PP
NULL
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
On success, return the number of records.
.PP
On error, exception will be thrown.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
when exception happen, use getLastError() to get the error code and use
getLastErrMsg() to get error message.
For more detial, please reference to Troubleshooting.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
Select the record that the age field value greater than (with using $gt) 20
under the collection, bar, and get the number of records from the current cursor
to the final cursor.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.foo.bar.find(\ {\ age:\ {\ $gt:\ 20\ }\ }\ ).size()
1
\f[]
.fi
